I"<p>Step one: running python3 instead of python2.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>alias python=python3
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Step one complete.</p>

<p>Next: Creating and cloning the git repository. Creating is straightforward; clone using following command:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo git clone https://github.com/USERNAME/REPONAME.git
</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li>sudo grants permission to run the command</li>
  <li>URL retrieved from “clone repository” option in browser</li>
  <li>make sure correct directory is set before running command</li>
  <li>permissions must be set for directory before work is able to be done within it</li>
</ul>

